         <div>
            <head>First steps in Oxygen</head>
            <list>
               <item>Open Oxygen XML Editor</item>
               <figure>
                  <graphic url="Graphics/BearOxygen.png" width="15cm"/>
                  <caption>Bear Oxygen XML Editor</caption>
               </figure>
               <item>Create a new XML document</item>
               <figure>
                  <graphic url="Graphics/OpenXMLdocumentDialogueBox.png" width="15cm"/>
                  <caption>Dialogue box when opening a new document - XML</caption>
               </figure>
               <figure>
                  <graphic url="Graphics/Bear%20XML%20document.png" width="15cm"/>
                  <caption>Bear XML document</caption>
               </figure>

            </list>
         </div>
         <div>
            <head>Basic understanding of an XML document</head>
            <list>
               <item>Understanding the XML declaration</item>
               <item> The various XML objects: <list>
                     <item>Simple element - text content</item>
                     <item>Embedded elements - parenthesizing - forbidden constructs</item>
                     <item>Empty elements</item>
                     <item>Mixed content</item>
                     <item>Attributes - simple, double quotes</item>
                  </list>
               </item>
               <item>Flexibility offered by the XML model: elements can be repeted iteratively, recursively</item>
               <item>Notion of well-formedness</item>
               <figure>
                  <graphic url="Graphics/crossing-the-streams.jpg" width="10cm"/>
               </figure>
               <item>Notion of namespace: <list>
                     <item>Namespace declaration (and usage): <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                           <test:element xmlns:test="http://myDomainName.org/ns"/>
                        </egXML>
                     </item>
                     <item>Default namespace: <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"><TEI
                              xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"/></egXML></item>
                     <figure>
                        <graphic url="Graphics/NamespaceDeclarationByKurosawa.jpg" width="10cm"/>
                     </figure>
                     <item>Namespace usage <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"
                        ><testmyElement/></egXML></item>
                     <item>Default namespace usage: <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                           <quote>Demain d√®s l'aube...</quote>
                        </egXML>
                     </item>
                     <figure>
                        <graphic url="Graphics/NamespaceUseByKurosawa.jpg" width="10cm"/>
                     </figure>
                     <item>Opening a new document => TEI all; looking at the default root element</item>
                  </list>
               </item>
            </list>
         </div>
         <div>
            <head>First steps in XPath</head>
            <list>
               <item>Understanding the notion of tree - root element</item>
               <item>Checking Oxygen configuration to track position in XPath</item>
               <figure>
                  <graphic url="Graphics/XPath%20configuration.png" width="15cm"/>
                  <caption>Setting up Oxygen to track position in XPath</caption>
               </figure>
               <item>Using a path to filter a document</item>
               <item>The basic axes: child, parent, descendant (or self), ancestor (or self), following (sibling),
                  preceding (sibling)</item>
               <item>Selecting an attribute</item>
            </list>
         </div>
